                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <supplied resp="#TA">
                           <placeName key="place_109469">SANTERDON</placeName>, Bucks.</supplied> Composition dated <origDate when="1240">1240</origDate> by which 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Croc</surname>
                        </persName> delivers to farm
               to the <orgName key="org_107015">abbot and convent of Thame</orgName> for 14 years, the whole of his land which he had in
               <placeName type="minor">Stonifelde</placeName> except the dowry of his mother, and other land in
               <placeName key="place_109290">Grave</placeName> which is called <placeName type="minor">Wardore</placeName>. 
               For this composition the abbot gave to the said Roger four marks.
               Witn. <persName>Sir <forename>Will</forename>. de <surname>Beauchamp</surname>
                        </persName>, etc.</p>
